Skive-V
=======

This repository is a fork of vLLM (https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm),
based on tag v0.23.0, commit 0fc695fc6d1d82e9a5ac6835ac8e4e1c83703665.
vLLM is licensed under the Apache License 2.0; its LICENSE file is retained
in this repository unchanged.

Modifications in this fork (SKIVE — value-aware, block-wise KV-cache eviction):
  * Added config/CLI flags: kv_evict_enabled, kv_evict_budget,
    kv_evict_num_sink_blocks, kv_evict_num_local_blocks
    (vllm/config/cache.py, vllm/engine/arg_utils.py).
  * Added the vllm/kv_evict/ package (block scoring, eviction policy,
    worker/scheduler integration).
  * Added eviction hooks in the V1 model runner (vllm/v1/worker/gpu_model_runner.py)
    and scheduler-side block reclaim in vllm/v1/engine/core.py.
  * Added a guard in the V2 model runner (vllm/v1/worker/gpu/model_runner.py)
    that raises if eviction is enabled (eviction is implemented for the V1
    runner only; set VLLM_USE_V2_MODEL_RUNNER=0).

With kv_evict_enabled=False (the default), behavior is identical to stock vLLM.
